8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 728, L.D. 1109, “An Act to Reduce Gun
10 Violence Casualties in Maine by Prohibiting the Possession of Large-capacity Ammunition
11 Feeding Devices”
12 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'An Act to Reduce Gun Violence Casualties in Maine by Prohibiting the Trafficking
14 of Large-capacity Ammunition Feeding Devices'
15 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
16 following:
17 'Sec. 1. 17-A MRSA §1060 is enacted to read:
18 §1060. Large-capacity ammunition feeding devices
19 1. As used in this section, unless the context otherwise indicates, the following terms
20 have the following meanings.
21 A. "Federally licensed firearm dealer" means a person or firm that is licensed or is
22 required to be licensed as a dealer under 18 United States Code, Section 923(a).
23 B. "Large-capacity ammunition feeding device" means a magazine, belt, drum, box,
24 tube, feed strip or similar device that has a capacity of, or that can be readily restored
25 or converted to accept, more than 20 rounds of ammunition.
26 2. A person is guilty of trafficking of a large-capacity ammunition feeding device if
27 that person intentionally or knowingly manufactures, imports, purchases, trafficks in, sells,
28 offers to transfer or transfers ownership of a large-capacity ammunition feeding device.
29 3. A person who violates subsection 2 commits a Class D crime.
30 4. This section does not apply to:
31 A. An active duty member of the Armed Forces of the United States or the National
32 Guard who is authorized to possess and carry a large-capacity ammunition feeding
33 device;
Page 1 - 132LR2138(03)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 728, L.D. 1109
1 B. An employed federal or state law enforcement officer who, whether on or off duty,
2 is authorized to possess and carry a large-capacity ammunition feeding device;
3 C. A large-capacity ammunition feeding device that is manufactured or sold solely for
4 use with a firearm that is determined to be a curio or relic, or antique, as those terms
5 are defined in 27 Code of Federal Regulations, Section 478.11; or
6 D. A federally licensed firearm dealer temporarily transporting a large-capacity
7 ammunition feeding device through the State to be sold or transferred to a person
8 outside of the State.'
9 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
10 number to read consecutively.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment changes the title of the bill and provides that the culpable state of
1133 mind required for someone to be guilty of trafficking of a large-capacity ammunition
1144 feeding device is intentionally or knowingly. The amendment also clarifies that a device is
1155 a large-capacity ammunition feeding device if it accepts more than 20 rounds of
1166 ammunition. Finally, the amendment removes references to disposal or modification of a
1177 lawfully possessed large-capacity ammunition feeding device.
